Project 3: 90° Digital Reflection Phase Shifter Bit (2.7–3.0 GHz)

**Objective:**  
Design a 90-degree digital reflection-type phase shifter using PIN diode switching, implemented in microstrip on RO4003™ (20 mil, 0.5 oz copper).

**Specifications:**
- Frequency Range: 2700–3000 MHz  
- Input/Output Impedance: 50 Ω  
- Return Loss (S11, S22) < -15 dB  
- Insertion Loss (S21) > -0.7 dB  
- Differential Phase Shift: 90° ± 4.5°  
- Minimum Line Width: > 4 mils  

**Implementation Highlights:**
- Based on Figure 11.13 from Pozar
- Skyworks DSG9500 PIN diodes modeled using Pozar's equivalent circuits
- 0402 sized real components used for biasing
- EM co-simulation including DC bias lines
- Realistic layout
